: MB, NT, NU, YT 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">USA</emphasis>
: AK - 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">Holarctic</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="299" pageNumber="300" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="299" pageNumber="300">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="299" pageNumber="300">
This species has long been known under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1844" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="299" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="299" pageNumber="300">Dyschirius nigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1844 in the North American literature.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
